SIMPLE: inertness
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Inertness
<hw>In*ert"ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Lack of activity or
exertion; habitual indisposition to action or motion; sluggishness;
apathy; insensibility.</def> <rj><au>Glanvill.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Laziness and <qex>inertness</qex> of mind.</q>
<rj><au>Burke.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Absence of the power of self-motion;
inertia.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inerudite</ent>⟦br⟧
